  "title": "chore(examples): implement e-commerce demo mobile design",
  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis implements the mobile design of the e-commerce demo. Since the theme we provide is desktop-first, I wrote the demo style desktop-first.\r\n\r\n## Preview\r\n\r\n[See preview →](https://deploy-preview-3866--instantsearchjs.netlify.com/examples/e-commerce)\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nI took some decisions on how to develop the mobile adaptation to the e-commerce demo. Let me know if you think that some are not appropriate.\r\n\r\n- I used `data-` attributes for multiple purposes.\r\n    - `data-widget=\"widget-name\"` to be explicit on which element is related to an InstantSearch widget (I didn't specified an `id`)\r\n    - `data-layout=\"mobile|desktop\"` to filter out the elements that shouldn't be displayed on mobile or desktop\r\n- SVGs have a `viewbox` attribute so that they can be scaled via CSS\r\n- Once the user refines the filters, it scrolls to the results container\r\n- `position: sticky;` is used for the button at the bottom of the filters panel but is not supported on iOS\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nHere are some notes on things that we can improve.\r\n\r\n- The correct breakpoint to trigger to the mobile design is to be defined by Nico\r\n- The animation is not great and I plan to revisit it. I'd appreciate some suggestions on how to make it look better.\r\n- The hit layout overflows on small screens (see page 3)\r\n- I'm not convinced with the chosen CSS naming so I'm in for suggestions\r\n\r\n## Related\r\n\r\n- [Design](https://app.zeplin.io/project/5acc8becfc0c980068fc12cc/screen/5d03a7333916305e0ad8e492)",
